---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="About Us | Hot Studio Gear">
	<div class="container about-container">
		
		<!-- Main Content Column -->
		<div class="about-main-col">
			<article class="card-parchment about-article">
				<header style="margin-bottom: 2rem; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-outline-variant); padding-bottom: 1.5rem;">
					<h1 class="page-title">About HotStudioGear.com</h1>
					<p class="hero-subhead">Serving the serious audio public, the almost-serious, and the spiritually prepared since Gary first realized the world was not ready for his final record.</p>
				</header>

				<!-- Hero Section -->
				<div class="content-section">
					<img src={`${base}/images/gary_founder_hero.png`} alt="Gary standing proudly in a cluttered living-room studio, one hand on a massive vintage console, looking like a founder who believes history has already begun to vindicate him." class="featured-image full-bleed" />
					<div class="text-body">
						<p class="dropcap">HotStudioGear.com was founded on a simple principle: the modern world has become dangerously casual about audio infrastructure.</p>
						<p>Where others saw a forgotten connector, Gary saw destiny. Where others saw a dusty rack unit, Gary saw unfinished business. Where others saw a Speak & Spell with one sticky button, Gary saw a rare educational tone engine whose time, frankly, is coming again.</p>
						<p>This is not just a parts site. It is the culmination of decades of near-breakthroughs, advanced technical restraint, selective industry involvement, and the kind of neighborhood-based creative leadership that only a few men are burdened with.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Our Story -->
				<div class="content-section">
					<h2>Our Story</h2>
					<div class="text-body">
						<p>Gary's journey began, as many important journeys do, with people underestimating him.</p>
						<p>As a teen, Gary understood—long before the culture did—that greatness could not be rushed through inadequate equipment. Lesser boys were out writing songs, forming bands, and embarrassingly releasing material before they had even learned basic cable discipline. Gary, by contrast, took the more difficult and visionary path: waiting.</p>
						<img src={`${base}/images/gary_youth_bedroom.png`} alt="A young Gary in a bedroom studio surrounded by ambitious but incomplete recording gear, already carrying himself like a misunderstood genius waiting for proper conditions." class="featured-image breakout-image-right" style="max-width: 50%; float: right; margin-left: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;" />
						<p>What began as a temporary pause until the right studio setup became available soon matured into a forty-plus-year research phase involving vintage consoles, obscure cable ends, synth repair parts, test gear, rack hardware, patchbays, rare manuals, discontinued adapters, tape machines of historical significance, and several fully justified detours into educational electronics.</p>
						<p>At no point was Gary "avoiding the work."</p>
						<p>He was protecting the work from premature exposure to mediocrity.</p>
						<div style="clear: both;"></div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Gary's Founder Statement -->
				<div class="content-section">
					<h2>Gary's Founder Statement</h2>
					<div class="text-body">
						<p>People sometimes ask me, "Gary, how did a man like you come to know so much about recording, signal flow, connectors, console topology, vintage gear logistics, and the deeper failures of the modern musician?"</p>
						<p>Well, I wouldn't know shit—except that over many decades I have had experiences most people only read about, or fail to correctly interpret when they happen right in front of them.</p>
						<blockquote class="pull-quote">"Honesty, when addressing the general public, sometimes requires a responsible degree of narrative assistance."</blockquote>
						<p>I've stood outside sessions that became important. I've exchanged meaningful glances with men whose names you would recognize if I thought they deserved the publicity. I have had prolonged technical disagreements with sales staff who later admitted, quietly and not in writing, that I was asking questions from a higher level. I have been in rooms adjacent to professional rooms. I have been invited, informally, to keep talking by people who were in no position to handle what I knew.</p>
						<p>So yes, in a sense, I come by this honestly. Though I have also learned that honesty, when addressing the general public, sometimes requires a responsible degree of narrative assistance.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Why We Exist -->
				<div class="content-section">
					<h2>Why We Exist</h2>
					<div class="text-body">
						<p>HotStudioGear.com exists because Gary saw that creative people were being failed by three corrupting influences:</p>
						<ol class="custom-list">
							<li><strong>Underbuilt signal chains:</strong> Too many people attempting greatness through casual wiring, random adapters, and connector choices that suggest a troubled upbringing.</li>
							<li><strong>A culture of premature output:</strong> Songs released before the artist has even finished reorganizing his patchbay philosophy.</li>
							<li><strong>A tragic lack of proper parts access:</strong> An entire generation wandering the earth without the correct belt, knob cap, DIN converter, BNC coupler, or TASCAM-pinout DB25 breakout.</li>
						</ol>
						<p>We are here to correct that.</p>
						<img src={`${base}/images/gary_parts_curator.png`} alt="Gary presenting a curated wall of obscure audio parts and cable ends as though unveiling a civilizational achievement." class="featured-image full-bleed" />
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Gary's Qualifications -->
				<div class="content-section">
					<h2>Gary's Qualifications</h2>
					<div class="text-body">
						<p>Gary is not merely a retailer. He is a figure of unusual preparedness. His qualifications include:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>over four decades of uninterrupted pre-production readiness</li>
							<li>deep familiarity with XLR, TRS, TS, RCA, BNC, MIDI DIN, insert Y-cables, bantam patching, DB25 snakes, and the emotional lives of all of them</li>
							<li>extensive experience explaining signal integrity to people who later pretended they already knew</li>
							<li>a practical understanding of vintage consoles, outboard gear, cable dressing, normalization logic, and why most home studios feel spiritually unfinished</li>
							<li>ownership of multiple notebooks containing album concepts in advanced developmental suspension</li>
							<li>recognized local authority status in matters of wire, hum, routing, rack screw selection, and connector seriousness</li>
						</ul>
						<blockquote class="pull-quote">"Because of my many contacts with industry bigwigs that owe me bigtime, I know what real readiness looks like."</blockquote>
						<p>Gary has also, through many contacts with industry bigwigs that owe him bigtime, developed an unusually refined instinct for what separates a casual setup from a truly consequential room. We do not name those individuals here, mainly to protect them from embarrassment and follow-up questions.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Our Miracle Neighborhood Advantage -->
				<div class="content-section">
					<h2>Our Miracle Neighborhood Advantage</h2>
					<img src={`${base}/images/gary_miracle_neighborhood.png`} alt="Gary outdoors in his supposedly miraculous creative neighborhood, gesturing as though he is the guardian of a local zone of artistic destiny." class="featured-image breakout-image-left" style="max-width: 50%; float: left; margin-right: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;" />
					<div class="text-body">
						<p>HotStudioGear.com operates from the heart of a miracle neighborhood favored, in ways both documented and subtle, by some of the world's most creative geniuses.</p>
						<p>There is something about the air here. Some say it is the light. Some say it is the tree cover. Some say it is the unusual electromagnetic calm created by Gary's careful cable storage practices. Whatever the cause, this neighborhood has long been a place where unusual minds feel permitted to remain unusual.</p>
						<p>In other districts, a man might be judged for converting his living room into a control environment or for maintaining several drawers of sorted connectors next to the good plates. Here, such commitment is not merely tolerated. It is sensed.</p>
						<p>Many of the world's boldest creative people, had circumstances aligned differently, could easily have ended up here. Gary did.</p>
						<p>That matters.</p>
						<div style="clear: both;"></div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Our Reputation & Claims to Fame -->
				<div class="content-section">
					<h2>Our Reputation</h2>
					<div class="text-body">
						<p>We are known for several things:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>rare and strangely specific inventory</li>
							<li>product descriptions that tell the truth more intensely than most people can process</li>
							<li>unusually high standards around cable categories and compatibility language</li>
							<li>emotionally mature levels of respect for patchbays</li>
							<li>founder-led insights drawn from a career that has remained just shy of public vindication for reasons too complex to trivialize here</li>
						</ul>
						<p>Customers trust us because Gary writes every listing from the standpoint of a man who has spent half a lifetime one decision away from history.</p>

						<h3>Frequently Implied Claims to Fame</h3>
						<p>While Gary is too modest to maintain a formal list of accomplishments, observers have noted that he has:</p>
						<img src={`${base}/images/gary_bored_guests.png`} alt="Gary in his living room studio explaining a technical point to politely trapped guests, convinced they are witnessing greatness." class="featured-image full-bleed" />
						<ul>
							<li>correctly identified a grounding problem before anyone else in the room admitted there was one</li>
							<li>advised multiple musicians, at varying distances, on what they should have done differently</li>
							<li>been regarded by at least one local repairman as "serious"</li>
							<li>nearly begun several major recording projects under conditions that, had the world been more patient, might have changed everything</li>
							<li>developed a cable organization approach some have described as excessive and others, more perceptive, as civilization itself</li>
							<li>maintained relationships with people adjacent to fame, some of whom continue to benefit from Gary's discretion</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Our Promise -->
				<div class="content-section" style="border-bottom: none;">
					<h2>Our Promise</h2>
					<div class="text-body">
						<p>We do not promise overnight success. Frankly, that kind of promise attracts the wrong customer.</p>
						<p>What we promise is better infrastructure, more dignified failure modes, and access to the sort of parts and guidance that help serious people postpone public disappointment until conditions are worthy of them.</p>
						<p>If you buy from us, you are not merely purchasing gear. You are aligning yourself with a higher standard of readiness.</p>
						<p>And when your moment comes—whether next month, next year, or after a strategically necessary four-decade delay—you will be glad you did not cut corners.</p>
					</div>
					<img src={`${base}/images/gary_obsessive_drawers.png`} alt="A close, impressive view of Gary's carefully arranged cable drawers, labeled bins, and founder tools, conveying the brand's oddly sincere obsession with readiness." class="featured-image full-bleed" />
				</div>
			</article>
		</div>

		<!-- Sidebar Column -->
		<aside class="sidebar-col">
			
			<div class="sidebar-widget">
				<h3>Gary In Brief</h3>
				<ul>
					<li>Founder, curator, signal-path thinker</li>
					<li>Pre-fame studio architect</li>
					<li>Connector realist</li>
					<li>Patchbay moralist</li>
					<li>Neighborhood-level creative force</li>
					<li>Respected by those qualified to know</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="sidebar-widget">
				<h3>Gary's Core Beliefs</h3>
				<ul>
					<li>The right cable is not detail. It is destiny.</li>
					<li>Output before readiness is vanity.</li>
					<li>Patchbays are a sign of civilization.</li>
					<li>Lesser minds confuse delay with lack of progress.</li>
					<li>A living room is wasted if it cannot route audio properly.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="sidebar-widget quote-widget">
				<blockquote>"I was never delaying the masterpiece. I was protecting it from inadequate infrastructure."</blockquote>
				<div class="quote-author">— Gary</div>
			</div>

			<div class="sidebar-widget cta-widget">
				<h3>Ready to improve your signal path before the world catches up?</h3>
				<p>Browse our rare parts, vintage oddities, and essential infrastructure for the serious almost-legend.</p>
				<button class="cta-button" onclick="window.location.href=`${base}/`">View Inventory</button>
			</div>

		</aside>

	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.about-container {
		padding-top: 3rem;
		padding-bottom: 3rem;
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 2.5fr 1fr;
		gap: 3rem;
	}

	.about-article {
		padding: 3rem;
		border-radius: 8px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.page-title {
		color: var(--color-surface-container-lowest);
		font-size: 3.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		line-height: 1.1;
		font-family: var(--font-display);
	}

	.hero-subhead {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		color: var(--color-primary-container);
		font-family: var(--font-headline);
		line-height: 1.3;
		border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary-container);
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.content-section {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		padding-bottom: 3rem;
		border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--color-outline-variant);
	}

	.content-section h2 {
		color: var(--color-surface-container-lowest);
		font-family: var(--font-headline);
		font-size: 2.2rem;
		margin-top: 0;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-primary-container);
		display: inline-block;
		padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}
	
	.content-section h3 {
		color: var(--color-surface-container-lowest);
		font-family: var(--font-headline);
		font-size: 1.6rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.text-body {
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: var(--color-surface-container-lowest);
	}

	.text-body p {
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.dropcap:first-letter {
		float: left;
		font-size: 4.5rem;
		line-height: 0.8;
		padding-top: 0.2rem;
		padding-right: 0.5rem;
		color: var(--color-primary-container);
		font-family: var(--font-display);
	}

	.featured-image {
		width: 100%;
		border-radius: 4px;
		box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		border: 4px solid var(--color-outline-variant);
	}

	.custom-list {
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		padding-left: 2rem;
	}
	
	.custom-list li {
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.pull-quote {
		border-left: 6px solid var(--color-primary-container);
		background: rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
		margin: 2.5rem 0;
		padding: 2rem;
		font-family: var(--font-headline);
		font-size: 1.7rem;
		font-style: italic;
		color: var(--color-surface-container-lowest);
		position: relative;
	}
	
	.pull-quote::before {
		content: "“";
		font-size: 6rem;
		color: var(--color-outline-variant);
		position: absolute;
		top: -1rem;
		left: 1rem;
		opacity: 0.3;
		font-family: serif;
	}

	/* Sidebar Styles */
	.sidebar-col {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 2rem;
	}

	.sidebar-widget {
		background: var(--color-surface-container-high);
		border: 2px solid var(--color-outline-variant);
		padding: 2rem;
		border-radius: 8px;
		color: var(--color-on-surface);
		box-shadow: 0 8px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
	}

	.sidebar-widget h3 {
		font-family: var(--font-headline);
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		color: var(--color-primary);
		margin-top: 0;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-outline-variant);
		padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.sidebar-widget ul {
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.sidebar-widget li {
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		font-size: 1rem;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.quote-widget {
		background: var(--color-surface-container-lowest);
		color: var(--color-on-surface);
		border: 4px solid #111;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.quote-widget blockquote {
		font-family: var(--font-headline);
		font-size: 1.3rem;
		font-style: italic;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 0;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.quote-author {
		font-family: var(--font-label);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		margin-top: 1rem;
		color: var(--color-primary);
		font-weight: bold;
		letter-spacing: 0.05em;
	}

	.cta-widget {
		background: linear-gradient(180deg, #b41340, #510017);
		color: white;
		border-color: #ffb800;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.cta-widget h3 {
		color: #ffb800;
		border-bottom: none;
		font-size: 1.6rem;
		line-height: 1.2;
	}
	
	.cta-widget p {
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.cta-button {
		background: #ffb800;
		color: #000;
		border: 2px solid #000;
		padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
		font-family: var(--font-label);
		font-weight: bold;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		cursor: pointer;
		width: 100%;
		box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
		transition: all 0.2s ease;
	}

	.cta-button:hover {
		background: #fff;
		transform: translateY(-2px);
		box-shadow: 0 6px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
	}

	/* Global Mobile Responsive Logic for About Page */
	@media (max-width: 900px) {
		.about-container { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
		.breakout-image-right, .breakout-image-left { float: none !important; max-width: 100% !important; margin-left: 0 !important; margin-right: 0 !important; }
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.about-container { padding-top: 0 !important; padding-bottom: 2rem !important; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; margin-top: 0; gap: 1rem; }
		.about-article { padding: 1.5rem 1rem; border-radius: 0; border: none; }
		.page-title { font-size: 2.5rem; }
		.hero-subhead { font-size: 1.2rem; }
		.text-body { font-size: 1.1rem; }
		
		.full-bleed, .breakout-image-right, .breakout-image-left {
			width: calc(100% + 2rem) !important;
			max-width: none !important;
			margin-left: -1rem !important;
			margin-right: -1rem !important;
			border-radius: 0;
			border-left: none;
			border-right: none;
		}

		.pull-quote {
			font-size: 1.3rem;
			padding: 1.5rem;
			margin-left: -1rem;
			margin-right: -1rem;
			border-radius: 0;
		}
		
		.sidebar-col { padding: 0 1rem; }
	}
</style>
